History

FIRST Global Challenge

AENTA, FIRST Tech Challenge Team 22940, is a team of students from the National School of Physics and Math, Almaty, Kazakhstan. The team was created in the summer of 2022 by 10th grade student Omar Aruzhan, who had experience in the FIRST LEGO League. Initially, AENTA consisted of five members. The name of the team is the initials of the names of the first squad members themselves. In the year of its creation, the team succeeded in many ways and won the Champion's Award at the National Stage of the FIRST Global Challenge in Kazakhstan.

{/*

FIRST Tech Challenge

A month later, Aruzhan decided to establish a team and participate in the FIRST Tech Challenge. At the moment the team consists of 10 members: Shakir, Adi, Zhanel, Ayana, Ayan, Aliman, Ramazan, Altynai, Yerasyl and Aruzhan. As you mentioned, our team’s topic is related to NASA. The main reason is location of NASA’s base. On of the important place of this company is located in Houston. There is parallel with our main goal. Passing the regional and republic tournaments lead us to participate in Houston’s international championship. Moreover, our team members are really keen on from astronomical and technological thematics. Because the future always pretends to make development in space. According to our thematic we also decided to make design of our merchandise related to NASA’s astronauts.
